      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for all five operating points; GCI < 5% on primary QoI (shear stress integral).",
      "rationale": "Three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 11.7M, 31.4M cells) were used. GCI values ranged from 1.8% to 4.3% across all operating points for the hemolysis-relevant shear stress QoI, satisfying the acceptance criterion. Asymptotic range confirmed (GCI ratio within 5% of unity)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions documented and traceable; temperature, hematocrit, and flow rate controlled within ±2% of nominal.",
      "rationale": "Bench test conditions were drawn from the FDA pump validation dataset. Inlet flow rates, rotational speeds, and fluid properties (bovine blood, Hct 33±1%) are fully documented. Environmental controls (temperature 37±0.5°C) recorded in laboratory notebooks and confirmed against CFD boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) within 15% of experimental mean across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values compared against experimental measurements from three independent test runs. Mean absolute percentage error was 8.3% across all five operating points. All predictions fell within the experimental uncertainty band (±1 SD). Achieved level exceeds required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress integral) are directly traceable to the decision QoI (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "The validation QoIs — normalized index of hemolysis and volume-averaged shear stress — are established surrogates for the decision-relevant RH metric. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) directly relates shear stress exposure to red blood cell damage, providing a clear mechanistic link. Relevance confirmed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties overlap with COU envelope; any extrapolation documented.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares the same impeller topology as the device under assessment. Operating points span the COU flow-speed envelope (2–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM). Fluid properties match COU specification. No significant extrapolation identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated; residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to normalized residuals below 1×10⁻⁵ for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Global mass imbalance was below 0.005% in all cases. Convergence histories archived in the simulation record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; checklist completed and signed.",
      "rationale": "An independent CFD analyst reviewed the simulation setup, boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and solver settings against a pre-defined checklist. No discrepancies identified. Review record retained in the project file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified with sensitivity study; hemolysis submodel literature support documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotating machinery flows. Sensitivity study comparing SST k-ω, realizable k-ε, and RSM showed less than 6% variation in NIH predictions. The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model is the standard in the field and supported by multiple independent validation studies. Model form uncertainty quantified and within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs traceable to measurements or literature; uncertainty in key inputs (viscosity, density) propagated to output.",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties derived from published bovine blood rheology data (Merrill et al.) consistent with bench test fluid. Geometric inputs extracted from manufacturer CAD files with dimensional verification against physical measurements. Sensitivity of NIH to ±5% variation in viscosity evaluated; output variation was 3.1%, within acceptable range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples (blood batches) characterized; batch-to-batch variability assessed and within ASTM F1841 limits.",
      "rationale": "Three independent bovine blood batches were used across validation experiments. Hematocrit (33±1%), plasma hemoglobin baseline (<5 mg/dL), and osmolality (290±10 mOsm/kg) confirmed for each batch per ASTM F1841. Batch-to-batch NIH variability was 4.7%, within the 10% acceptance limit."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that equivalency of input parameters does not apply to this COU because the CFD model uses directly measured boundary conditions from the bench test rather than inferred or transferred parameters from a different experimental context. Consequently, no formal equivalency assessment was conducted and this factor was carried forward without evaluation. The factor is considered non-contributory to the overall credibility determination."
    }
